Content: 
<strong>LifeSim</strong> is an interactive evolutionary sandbox where you watch, or influence, digital organisms evolve over hundreds of generations. Cells compete for resources, reproduce with genetic variation, and adapt to their environment.<br><br>
You can observe passively or intervene directly. Inspect or modify any cell's genetics, and directly control their behavior. Force mutations. Infect or cure populations. Endless simulations, in an infinite space.;
Card:
<h4 class="subtitle">How is it different?</h4>
<ul class="list">
    <li>Behaviors, interactions, & speciation are all emergent from simple rules, & never the same twice.</li>
    <li>Immunity, predation, and reproduction compete as evolutionary pressures that spur continuous adaptation.</li>
    <li>Viruses mutate independently inside hosts, & follow genetic lineages, forcing an evolutionary arms race.</li>
</ul>;
Description: 
<em>In <strong>LifeSim</strong>, there are no predetermined outcomes. Watch real emergence arise from genetic variance and viral pressure.</em>;
